[[Image:ThomasBGuest23.jpg|thumb|right|Thomas B. Guest <br> Source: Library and Archives Canada]]

'''Thomas B. Guest''' was an [[Ontario]] political figure. He represented [[Perth South]] in the [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]] from 1871 to 1874.

He served as reeve of [[St. Mary's, Ontario|St. Mary's]] in 1855 to 1856, warden for [[Perth County, Ontario|Perth County]] in 1856 and mayor of St. Mary's in 1864. He was also lieutenant-colonel of the local militia.

